OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 27 Mar to Sun 5 Apr
OL,6,FStill rather changeable at the start
OL,7,Fof this period, with further frontal
OL,8,Fsystems moving across the UK, bringing
OL,9,Frain and stronger winds at times.
OL,10,FThrough late March, high pressure is
OL,11,Flikely to be located to the southwest
OL,12,Fof UK, with a predominantly westerly
OL,13,For northwesterly airstream in place.
OL,14,FFurther weather fronts are likely to
OL,15,Fround this high, bringing occasional
OL,16,Frain to the north and perhaps east of
OL,17,Fthe country, whereas areas further
OL,18,Fsouthwest stand a better chance of
OL,19,Fbeing drier. In this setup,
OL,20,Ftemperatures will probably pan out
OL,21,Fclose to average overall, with some
OL,22,Fovernight frost where skies are clear
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fand winds light. Into early April and
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fhigh pressure may become rather more
OL,25,Fdominant, with many areas seeing dry,
OL,26,Fsettled conditions.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
